    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="292"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.20/174</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Berle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Iranian Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schayesteh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-23">October 23,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: I refer to your recent inquiry
                    regarding the possibility of obtaining at this time two American Army officers
                    as advisers to the Iranian Army on military aviation and engineering. The War
                    Department has now informed the Department that it prefers to defer
                    consideration of this matter pending receipt of a report from Major General
                    Ridley, who has been instructed to make a thorough survey of the needs of the
                    Iranian Army with respect to American military advisers. The Department of State
                    and the War Department are prepared, of course, to give sympathetic attention to
                    any recommendations which may be made by General Ridley in this regard, within
                    the limitations imposed by the personnel needs of the combatant forces of the
                    United Nations.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>A. A. <hi rend="smallcaps">Berle, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
